<subSubSection id="C34E6570FF8DFFD1C0EBF92513C30438" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8DFFD1C0EBF92513C30438" blockId="4.[151,1437,1681,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8DFFD1C0EBF925116E05A8" bold="true" box="[151,273,1681,1706]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8DFFD1C15FF92511D405A8" box="[291,427,1681,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Body length 8.0–9.0 mm. Upper margin of mystax rounded in frontal view, reaching antennal sockets, distance between mystax and antennal sockets longer than scape and pedicel combined. Postocular setae not abundant. Antenna dark brown, sometimes pedicel reddish. Thorax black. Anepisternum anterodorsally without hairs, postpronotal lobe with short hairs. Dorsocentral setae long, distinct, reaching transverse suture. Scutellum with short white setae. Hypopygium black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34E6570FF8DFFD2C0BBF8F1120C0244" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="424" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8DFFD1C0BBF8F113E604EC" blockId="4.[151,1437,1681,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8DFFD1C0BBF8F111DB045C" bold="true" box="[199,420,1861,1886]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Description. Male.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8DFFD1C1D7F8F11197045C" box="[427,488,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Head</emphasis>
black. Face below antennal sockets narrow, 0.21–0.23 × as wide as head. Face with silvery tomentum. Antenna dark brown, sometimes pedicel reddish, scape and pedicel with some white bristles. Hairs and setae of head white. Upper margin of mystax rounded in frontal view, reaching antennal sockets, distance between mystax and antennal sockets longer than scape and pedicel combined (
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8DFFD1C454F805140204C8" box="[1064,1149,1969,1994]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Postocular setae few in number. Palpus black with long white hairs, but shorter than mystax.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFF2314C0023D" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFF23116703B2" box="[199,280,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Thorax</emphasis>
black, postpronotal lobe in some 
<typeStatus id="54EF8859FF8CFFD0C2ECFF2C128403B2" box="[656,763,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">paratypes</typeStatus>
dark brown. Scutum with greyish tomentum and two darker lateral spots of tomentum and darker paramedian and median stripes, with few short white hairs. Postpronotal lobe with short hairs as on scutum. Anepisternum anterodorsally without hairs, one 
<typeStatus id="54EF8859FF8CFFD0C468FF54140B03FA" box="[1044,1140,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">paratype</typeStatus>
with 1–3 short hairs (
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8CFFD0C513FF6B10C9021E" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Dorsocentral setae long, distinct, reaching or even crossing transverse suture, supra-alar setae long, reaching transverse suture (
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8CFFD0C11EFE93119B0242" box="[354,484,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Scutellum on margin with 15 or less short scutellar white setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFEF912ED0267" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" box="[199,658,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFEF911750266" box="[199,266,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Wings</emphasis>
clear, iridescence, halteres yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFEC512A602CD" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFEC51083028A" box="[199,252,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Legs</emphasis>
. Coxa black with grayish tomentum and white setae. Trochanter reddish, fore- and mid-femur black, hind femur dark brown, tibia brownish, paler than hind femur, tarsus black, femur and tibia with reddish spot with indistinct boundary. Leg with white hairs and setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFE6814CC011A" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFE68114E02F7" box="[199,305,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites black with greyish tomentum and short white hairs, some tergites posteriorly and laterally reddish, sternites paler than tergites. Tergites along median line with dark stripe without hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFD9111240186" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFD911129013E" box="[199,342,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Hypopygium</emphasis>
large, well visible, black with white hairs, slightly turned (
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8CFFD0C46FFD9014E2013F" box="[1043,1181,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[327,1266,799,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Gonostyle distinctly curved at a right angle at the apex, with few hairs (
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8CFFD0C28EFDF313060162" box="[754,889,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,991,1014]" captionTargetBox="[360,1227,224,955]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,213,961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Line drawings of male genitalia of Habropogon lehri sp. nov., holotype. 16, 17. Hypopygium, lateral (16) and dorsal (17) view. 18 – 20. The same gonocoxite in different views. 21. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847952/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Figs 16–20</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apodeme shorter than endoaedeagal process (
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8CFFD0C086FDD811320186" box="[250,333,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,991,1014]" captionTargetBox="[360,1227,224,955]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,213,961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Line drawings of male genitalia of Habropogon lehri sp. nov., holotype. 16, 17. Hypopygium, lateral (16) and dorsal (17) view. 18 – 20. The same gonocoxite in different views. 21. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847952/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFD3B12ED01A5" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" box="[199,658,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFD3B112901AA" bold="true" box="[199,342,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Body length</emphasis>
8.0–9.0 (
<typeStatus id="54EF8859FF8CFFD0C1BCFD3B125B01AA" box="[448,548,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">holotype</typeStatus>
8.5) mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0BBFD0011E801F2" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0BBFD00115A01CF" bold="true" box="[199,293,692,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Female.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136F2A7EFF8CFFD0C14BFD0011F101CE" box="[311,398,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 23. 22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[384,1207,1112,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1247,1104,1911]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 23. 22. Habropogon lehri sp. nov., ♀, paratype, lateral view. 23. Distribution of Habropogon species (based on the current material and Lehr 1960, Astakhov 2015)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847954/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Similar to male except hairs and setae more dense on postsutural scutum and scutellum, terminalia dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2B6673FF8CFFD0C0EBF8CA123504B1" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847950/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="422" targetBox="[327,1263,800,1887]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8CFFD0C0EBF8CA123504B1" blockId="5.[151,1436,1918,1971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C0EBF8CA11290496" bold="true" box="[151,342,1918,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">FIGURES 12–15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C544D78FF8CFFD0C123F8CA12670496" authority="Lelej, 2017" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2017" box="[351,536,1918,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Habropogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C123F8CA12670496" box="[351,536,1918,1940]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">Habropogon lehri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2135792FF8CFFD0C25DF8CB120B0496" box="[545,628,1919,1940]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B920EAE9FF8CFFD0C25DF8CB120B0496" bold="true" box="[545,628,1919,1940]" pageId="5" pageNumber="422">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂, holotype. 12. Head, frontal view. 13. Anepisternum, lateral view. 14, 15. Habitus, lateral (14) and dorsal (15) views.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2B6673FF8FFFD3C0EBFC6B14100716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847952/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="423" targetBox="[360,1227,224,955]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BEB36FBFF8FFFD3C0EBFC6B14100716" blockId="6.[151,1436,991,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="423">
